1. *Magija* je drevna umetnost koja se bavi tajanstvenim silama. (*Magija* is an ancient art that deals with mysterious forces.) 
2. Ovaj predmet ima neku čudnu *magiju* koja privlači ljude da ga kupuju. (This object has a strange *magic* that attracts people to buy it.)
3. Ona je prava *magičarka*, u stanju je da izvede neverovatne trikove. (She is a real *magician*, able to perform incredible tricks.)
4. Njihovu vezu prati *magijska* privlačnost, kao da su predodređeni jedno za drugo. (Their relationship is accompanied by a *magical* attraction, as if they were meant for each other.)
5. U filmu se pojavljuju različiti likovi sa *magičnim* moćima, koji su u stanju da kontrolišu vreme i prostor. (The film features various characters with *magical* powers, who can control time and space.)
6. Nekada se verovalo da se *magija* može koristiti za lečenje bolesti, ali to nije dokazano. (It was once believed that *magic* could be used to cure illnesses, but this has not been proven.)
7. *Magija* izgleda lepo u filmovima, ali u stvarnom životu to je opasno i može nauditi ljudima. (*Magic* looks beautiful in movies, but in real life, it is dangerous and can harm people.)
8. Deca su oduševljena kada ih roditelji vode u *magični* park sa atrakcijama i čarobnim predstavama. (Children are thrilled when their parents take them to a *magical* park with attractions and magical performances.)
9. Čitanje knjiga o *magiji* može biti zabavno i edukativno iskustvo za decu. (Reading books about *magic* can be a fun and educational experience for children.)
10. Postoji mnogo različitih vrsta *magije*, kao što su crna, bela, ritualna, i druge. (There are many different types of *magic*, such as black, white, ritual, and others.)